      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LONDON'S IMAGE (1) just missed over 1400m in the Bunbury Stakes most recently when beaten by Bonjoy who went on with the job following that run. Back to 1200m now is a big tick and this looks to set up nicely for her off a short freshen. Fiore knows her well and she can get back to winning ways. BLACK ORA (7) was very good fresh when flying home to just miss over 1000m, and we'll get a guide on that form earlier in the card. Pike rides her down in the weights and she steps out to 1200m for the first time in a while. The inside draw can see her sit a touch closer and she'll be hard to hold out if the gaps come. CESSATION (6) will be fitter for the fresh run in the Rock Magic Stakes and is better suited out to this trip now. Has enough speed to roll across from out wide and can be in this for a long way. PETULA (2) can improve sharply with the blinkers going on today.",
